Welcome to Purdue Fencing

Purdue Fencing Club is a co-ed club sports team. We are proud to represent Purdue at collegiate tournaments with men and women squads for foil, epee, and saber. We provide experiences in fencing, competition, and camaraderie to all Boilermakers who show interest.

Nearly one hundred years ago, we humbly began as a 5-member men's varsity foil squad in 1922. As the varsity squad gained popularity, in 1935, an honorary fraternal order, Silver Mask, formed. In 1970, men's varsity fencing would dissolve into Purdue Fencing Club in its modern form. Since then, Purdue Fencing Club continues to grow and we now have over 50 members!
